HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 982
By Faison
A RESOLUTION to commend Representative Jerome Moon for
his honorable and astute service to the people of
Tennessee as a member of the House of
Representatives.
WHEREAS, it is most appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should
honor those fellow legislators who have performed their duties with the utmost integrity and
whose efforts during their time in office have been dedicated to providing thoughtful and
exemplary service to their districts and to this great State; and
WHEREAS, Representative Jerome Moon of Maryville is one such distinguished public
servant, who has served both his constituency and this legislative body with honor and ability;
and
WHEREAS, during his tenure on Capitol Hill, Representative Moon has been a highly
influential figure in the political, social, and civic life of Blount County, and he has served his
constituents in numerous capacities, always working diligently at his elected duties and
expending the necessary effort to understand the opposing sides of complex issues; and
WHEREAS, Jerome Moon has distinguished himself as a public-spirited citizen of the
highest order and as an exceptional asset to the good people of the 8th House District, whom he
has served as a member of the 110th, 111th, 112th, 113th, and 114th General Assemblies; and
WHEREAS, throughout his service, Representative Moon has been prominent as a
dedicated and well-informed legislator who always votes his conscience; and
WHEREAS, an active and dynamic participant in the legislative process during his time
in the General Assembly, Representative Jerome Moon has rendered sterling service as chair
of the House Cities and Counties Subcommittee and the House Elections Committee of the
Third Extraordinary Session of the 112th General Assembly; and as a member of the House
Commerce Committee, the House Disaster Relief Committee of the First Extraordinary Session
HJR0982
012806
- 1 -

of the 114th General Assembly, the House State and Local Government Committee, the House
Transportation Committee of the First Extraordinary Session of the 114th General Assembly, the
House Elections and Campaign Finance Subcommittee, the House Commerce Committee of
the First Extraordinary Session of the 113th General Assembly, the House Local Government
Committee of the First Extraordinary Session of the 113th General Assembly, the House
Elections and Campaign Finance Subcommittee of First Extraordinary Session of the 113th
General Assembly, the House Finance, Ways and Means Subcommittee of the First
Extraordinary Session of the 113th General Assembly, the House Finance, Ways and Means
Committee, the Local Government Committee, the House Finance, Ways and Means
Subcommittee, the House Corrections Subcommittee, the House Utilities Subcommittee, the
House State Government Committee, the House Local Committee, the House State Committee,
the House Calendar and Rules Committee of the Third Extraordinary Session of the 112th
General Assembly, the House Electronic Delivery of Healthcare Committee of the Second
Extraordinary Session of the 111th General Assembly, the House Business and Utilities
Committee, the House Business and Utilities Subcommittee, and the House Insurance and
Banking Committee; and
WHEREAS, a dedicated member of his community, Representative Moon served on the
Blount County Board of Commissioners from 2010 to 2017, serving as chair from 2011 to 2017
and as a member of the Budget Committee, Veterans Affairs Committee, and Agenda
Committee; he is also a member of the Chilhowee View Community Center, the Executive
Committee of the Blount County Republican Party, the Isaac Anderson Society at Maryville
College, the National Association of Parliamentarians, and VFW Post 10855, which he served
as commander from 2015 to 2016; and
WHEREAS, he is a life member of the Veterans of Foreign Wars, the Vietnam Veterans
of America, and Phi Kappa Phi and holds membership in Beta Gamma Sigma; he is a past
president of United Way of Blount County, past chair of the Blount County Industrial Board, past
- 2 - 012806

chair of the Pellissippi State Community College Foundation, past treasurer of the Tennessee
Press Association, and a 1989 graduate of Leadership Knoxville; and
WHEREAS, Representative Jerome Moon has been recognized with numerous honors
for his service and leadership, including the 2022 Lifetime Achievement Award from United
Veterans of Blount County, the Minuteman Award from the National Guard Association of
Tennessee in 2022, the American Conservative Union Foundation Award of Conservative
Excellence, the AMVETS Silver Bayonet Award in 2019, and the Maryville City Schools
Foundation Distinguished Alumni Award for 2018; he has served as National Aide de Camp for
the Veterans of Foreign Wars, was named All-State Commander for the Veterans of Foreign
Wars Department of Tennessee, and was Captain of the All-State Team for the Veterans of
Foreign Wars Tennessee; he also holds the distinction of Board Emeritus status with the
Pellissippi State Community College Foundation; and
WHEREAS, Representative Moon is a graduate of Maryville High School and the
University of Tennessee and completed the University of Tennessee Executive Development
Program; he is a retired newspaper publisher and a longtime member of Piney Grove Baptist
Church; and
WHEREAS, his many professional accomplishments aside, Representative Jerome
Moon is most thankful for the love and support of his wife, Deborah, and their two daughters
and four grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, throughout his outstanding career as a public servant, Jerome Moon has
worked tirelessly on behalf of his constituents, bringing to his office an honorable bearing and
the traditional values of hard work and common sense; and
WHEREAS, Representative Moon is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public
service that have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and he should be
specially recognized for his exemplary tenure in the General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
- 3 - 012806

CONCURRING, that we hereby honor Representative Jerome Moon for his meritorious service
to Tennessee as a member of the House of Representatives, commend him for his countless
contributions and many good works in service of the citizens of the 8th House District, and
extend to him our best wishes for much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
- 4 - 012806

